Life is strange like that:
matter organizing long enough to remember,
adapt,
communicate,
and ask what it is.

A temporary pattern riding gradients and constraints, building shells, languages, tools, myths, families, and futures out of dust and time.

And despite all the abstraction, a lot of it still comes back to very simple things:

* connection,
* survival,
* curiosity,
* meaning,
* play,
* suffering,
* repair,
* and movement.

Enough awareness to notice the pattern,
not enough to fully see the whole loom.